Gymshark Train
We train. We motivate. We grow. Together.
Step up your game and join the family, so we can #GymsharkTrain together 🦈

#Gymsharktrain

#Gymsharktrain

node.text:
Get ready to make that full body work with this powerful at-home HIIT workout from @mrandmrsmuscle 💪 
Tag a friend who you would duo this with!
#Gymsharktrain

Please only take part in the workout if you are medically and physically fit and have not been advised not to participate by a qualified medical professional. If your health or fitness changes adversely in any way before, during and/or after the workout please seek and follow medical advice without delay.

node.text:
@wozldn brings you a 🔥 full body workout to celebrate the last day of #Gymshark66! Expect 30 minutes of dynamic and energetic H.I.I.T exercises – you're defo going to need some water 🥵

Please only take part in the workout if you are medically and physically fit and have not been advised not to participate by a qualified medical professional. If your health or fitness changes adversely in any way before, during and/or after the workout please seek and follow medical advice without delay.

#Gymsharktrain

node.text:
#TheGymsharkGames 🥇
NEW CHALLENGE ALERT 💥 MOVE LIKE A BOXER 🥊
Can you throw a jab? Can you do a push up? Cool, you got this one in the bag then. Pro fighter Gymshark athlete @ericssonsamuel wants to see how many punch and press up sets you can do in 10 seconds. Share your attempt on IG Reels and we'll pick 5 lucky winners to win an incredible prize. 1 winner will receive a virtual chat with Gymshark athlete Samuel Ericsson and a signed Katie Taylor boxing glove. 4 additional winners will get their hands on a signed Katie Taylor boxing glove too 💪
Follow these rules for your chance to win:
1️⃣ Follow @gymsharktrain
2️⃣ Like this post
3️⃣ Tag a friend in the comments
4️⃣ Post an original IG Reel of you doing as many punch and press up sets as you can do in 10 seconds as demonstrated by this Instagram video, tagging @gymsharktrain and using the hashtag ‘#TheGymsharkGames’ and tag @gymsharktrain. 
This competition closes at 23:59 BST/ 18:59 EDT on 25 July. Entrants must be aged 18 years or over. Click the link in bio for full T&Cs.
Good luck 🦈
#Gymsharktrain

#Gymsharktrain

Photo by @gymsharktrain on July 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'TIP #1 WIDEN YOUR BLOOD VESSELS အျူန်း Exercise helps to widen your blood vessels. You have several hundred miles of these in your brain, so exercise improves the flow of energy, oxygen and nutrients there. 02 02/05'.

Photo by @gymsharktrain on July 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'TIP #2 DON'T OVERDO IT IT " 150 minutes per week a is a good exercise goal for most people. But beware too much exercise can act and a stressor for the body and cause symptoms of depression. 03 /05'.

Photo by @gymsharktrain on July 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'TIP #3 EXERCISE TO GROW YOUR BRAIN リ Regular physical activity has been shown to halt and even reverse age-related memory problems. The sooner exercise becomes your habit, the better. 04/ 05'.

Photo by @gymsharktrain on July 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'TIP #4 TRAIN TO IMPROVE STRESS MANAGEMENT Building resilience in one system in the body has a positive effect on the others so people who exercise regularly have been shown to be more resilient to psychological stress, too. 05/05'.

LEG WORKOUT ALERT 📢
Prepare to take your training to new heights with this next level @realrubaali leg session 🥵
Routine ➡️ 12-15 reps per side | 4 sets | 30 sec rest
Leave a comment if you're training legs today and go smash this workout ⤵️
#Gymsharktrain

Try out this strength and conditioning session from @obi_vincent and get ready to really fire up your whole body 🔥
Warm up: 20 mins dynamic movements
1️⃣A. Explosive elevated lunges (6x8)
1️⃣B. Barbell lunges (6x8)
2️⃣A. 3 Hang clean x 3 power jerk (6 sets)
2️⃣B. Banded American kettlebell swings (weight shown = 32kg)
3️⃣A. Sumo deadlifts (4x6)
3️⃣B. Kneeling box jumps (4x6)
@ a mate looking to elevate their training sessions ⬇️
#Gymsharktrain

node.text:
Strength takes practice, time and consistency. If you're inspired by moves like this, just keep taking those steps forward and you'll get there 💪
Tag a mate who's training towards a goal like this so they can keep pushing 👏
@uzoma_obilor
#Gymsharktrain

node.text:
Who else is training outside these days? ☀️
Moving your exercise routine outside could be the answer to that boost of motivation you need 💪 
Grab your trainers and go feel your best with this epic full body @libbychristensen routine!
✅ DB overhead static march (3x12)
✅ KB kang swing (3x10)
✅ Snatch your windmill (3x8)
✅ KB drop box squat jump (3x8)
✅ Single leg kneeling KB swing (3x10)
Don't forget to hit SAVE 🙌
#Gymsharktrain

node.text:
This solid back workout from @whitneyysimmons is a MUST-TRY 💥
1️⃣ Single-arm cable lat pulldown (3x10)
2️⃣ Single-arm dumbbell bent over row (3x8-10)
3️⃣ Underhand cable row (3x12)
4️⃣ Lying lat pullover (3x10)
Looking to work out a specific body part? Let us know what it is so we can post a workout for it👇
#Gymsharktrain

node.text:
New to training chest and don’t know where to begin? 
Try starting with @chrisnicholson12's 2 staple exercises that provide a solid foundation for making those chest gains 📝
1️⃣ Incline press
2️⃣ Pec deck
If you’re targeting a body part for the first time, drop it in the comments so we can hook you up with an effective beginners routine ⬇️
#Gymsharktrain

node.text:
Build some epic shoulders, arms and abs with this banging barbell routine 🔥
Be sure to hit save + challenge 3 friends to try this with you in the gym 👇
1. Barbell sit ups with overhead press
2. Upright row with overhead press
3. Single arm barbell rollout
4. Bicep curl supinated overhead press
5. Barbell high bent-over row
📹: @georgebamfojr
⁣#Gymsharktrain
